990
Your Honor,

I stand before you today with a sense of humility and remorse. I acknowledge my guilt in the matter at hand and, with a heavy heart, I plead guilty to the charge of attempting to shoplift a dress worth approximately 2000 pounds.

I recognize the seriousness of my actions and the impact it has had on the store and the individuals involved. I want to assure the court that my involvement in this offense was a singular incident, and I have no prior criminal record.

At the time of the incident, I faced a difficult decision. I desired a beautiful dress for prom, an event that holds great significance to me. However, I was fully aware that I did not possess the financial means to purchase it. Despite my circumstances, I deeply regret resorting to an unlawful act in an attempt to obtain the dress. I now understand the gravity of my actions and the consequences they entail.

I am sincerely remorseful for the pain I have caused to the store and its staff. It is my genuine intention to learn from this experience and make every effort to prevent such actions from happening again.

I understand that my guilty plea, as a first-time offender, is itself a significant mitigating factor. I ask the court to consider my remorse and my commitment to personal growth and contribution to society. I assure Your Honor that I have already taken steps to make amends for my actions and will continue to do so in the future.

Thank you for allowing me the opportunity to address the court today. I humbly request your leniency and compassion as I strive to learn from this mistake and work towards becoming a responsible and productive member of society.

